race.comment: HARLEQUIN PRANCER (6) won well fresh before a 1L defeat over the 1200m journey here most recently. She usually dips second-up, so her running well there shapes nicely for this. Third-up now, 1300m won't be an issue and she can land the knockout blow. DAINTY ROSE (8) flew home to win first-up before a disappointing effort most recently when finishing behind HARLEQUIN PRANCER. Blinkers come off now, but the rise to 1300m journey is ideal now and she can bounce back to form. BIONDO (3) gets the nose roll on for the first time today after he closed steadily over 1400m last time out. Third-up now and gets the in-form Wheatley on board. Can feature in the finish. COULDABEENAHANDBAG (7) was too good first-up as a $26 chance but there's no reason why she can't go on with the job. MISTRESS OF EXCESS (11) is better than she showed last time out and can bounce back to form.
